This is a '''list of GIS data sources''' (including some [[geoportal]]s) that provide information sets that can be used in [[geographic information system]]s (GIS) and [[spatial database]]s for purposes of [[geospatial analysis]] and [[cartographic]] mapping. This list categorizes the sources of interest.
== Global == {| class="wikitable sortable" style="text-align: left; color: black;" |+ '''GIS data for global datasets''' |- ! data-sort-type="text" | '''Name''' !! class="unsortable" | '''Description''' |- | align="left" | '''[[Natural Earth]]''' || Public domain [[vector graphics|vector]] and [[raster graphics|raster]] dataset. Supported by the [[NACIS]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.naturalearthdata.com/ |title=Natural Earth project website |publisher=Natural Earth |accessdate=23 July 2013}}</ref> |- | align="left" | '''[[Global Map]]''' || Provides consistent coverage of all the Earth's [[land cover]] area. Includes different thematic maps such as: transportation, elevation, drainage, vegetation, administrative boundaries, land cover, population centres, and land use. ''Registration required''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iscgm.org/cgi-bin/fswiki/wiki.cgi?page=Summary |title=Summary of Global Map |publisher=International Steering Committee for Global Mapping |accessdate=23 July 2013}}</ref> |- | align="left" | '''[[UNEP Environmental Data Explorer]]''' || Includes global forest cover, global potential [[evapotranspiration]], global average monthly temperatures, dams, [[Drainage basin|watershed]] boundaries, and much more. Use the advanced search to select geospatial data sets. Provided by the [[United Nations Environment Programme]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://geodata.grid.unep.ch/ |title=Environmental Data Explorer |publisher=[[United Nations Environment Programme]] |accessdate=23 July 2013}}</ref> |- | align="left" | '''[[GSHHG]]''' || [[Global Self-consistent, Hierarchical, High-resolution Shoreline Database]]: high quality, and consistent data.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/mgg/shorelines/gshhs.html |title=GSHHG |publisher=[[National Geophysical Data Center]] |accessdate=23 July 2013}}</ref> |- | align="left" | [http://asterweb.jpl.nasa.gov/gdem.asp '''ASTER GDEM'''] || 30m resolution global elevation data derived from [[Advanced Spaceborne Thermal Emission and Reflection Radiometer]] satellite images.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jspacesystems.or.jp/ersdac/GDEM/E/index.html |title=ASTER Global Digital Elevation Model |publisher=Japan Space Systems |accessdate=23 July 2013}}</ref> |- | align="left" | [http://www.opentopography.org/ '''OpenTopography'''] || High-resolution, [[Earth science]]-based, [[topography]] data, and related tools and resources. Available as dense [[point clouds]] and [[DEM]]s. |- | align="left" | [http://gisclimatechange.ucar.edu/ '''NCAR GIS Climate Change Scenarios'''] || Includes data used by the [[Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change|IPCC]] in their reports. Operated by the [[National Center for Atmospheric Research]]. ''Registration required''. |- | align="left" | [http://iridl.ldeo.columbia.edu/ '''IRI/LDEO Climate Data Library'''] || Collection of more than 300 datasets from various climate models and datasets. Operated by [[The Earth Institute]] and [[Lamont–Doherty Earth Observatory]]. |- | align="left" | [http://www.globalclimatemonitor.org/ '''Global Climate Monitor'''] || Climate web viewer containing accessible climatic information from 1901 that can be downloaded in a variety of GIS formats. |- | align="left" | [http://hydrosheds.cr.usgs.gov/ '''HydroSHEDS'''] || Global [[hydrological]] data based on the [[Shuttle Radar Topography Mission|SRTM]] elevation data. Includes river networks, watershed boundaries, drainage directions, and flow accumulations. |- | align="left" | [http://landcover.usgs.gov/ '''USGS Land Cover Institute'''] || Set of links from the [[USGS]] for numerous [[land cover]] datasets. Although primarily US data, further down the list there is data for other continents. |- | align="left" | [http://www.sage.wisc.edu/atlas/maps.php '''Atlas of the Biosphere: Mapping the Biosphere'''] || Raster maps of environmental variables including soil pH, potential evapotranspiration, average snow depth, and more. |- | align="left" | [http://worldwildlife.org/publications/global-200 '''Global 200'''] || Vector data from [[World Wide Fund for Nature|WWF]] of "a set of the Earth's terrestrial, freshwater, and marine ecoregions that harbor exceptional biodiversity and are representative of its ecosystems."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://worldwildlife.org/publications/global-200 |title=WWF's Global 200 project |publisher=[[World Wide Fund for Nature]] |accessdate=3 November 2013}}</ref> |- | align="left" | [http://worldwildlife.org/pages/global-lakes-and-wetlands-database '''Global Lakes and Wetlands Database'''] || Vector data created from multiple sources by the [[World Wide Fund for Nature|WWF]] and Center for Environmental Systems Research, [[University of Kassel]] outlining global wetlands, swamps, bogs, reservoirs, etc. |- | align="left" | [http://maps.tnc.org/gis_data.html '''Conservation GIS Data'''] || Data from [[The Nature Conservancy]] and associated organizations, including: TNC Lands & Waters (properties/preserves, easements and leases), Ecoregional Portfolio, Terrestrial [[Ecoregion]]s of the World, Freshwater Ecoregions of the World, and Marine Ecoregions of the World. |- | align="left" | [http://www.conservation.org/hotspots '''The Biodiversity Hotspots'''] || Data from [[Conservation International]] on areas of the world with especially high [[endemism]] and high numbers of [[threatened species]]. |- | align="left" | [http://www.wri.org/publication/pilot-analysis-global-ecosystems-1#data '''Pilot Analysis of Global Ecosystems: Forest Ecosystems'''] || Data from the [[World Resources Institute]] includes: percentage tree-cover, population density and tree cover, share of wood in fuel consumption, etc. |- | align="left" | [https://web.archive.org/web/20140408125147/http://soilgrids1km.isric.org/ '''SoilGrids1km - soil property and class maps'''] || SoilGrids1km is a collection of updatable soil property and class maps of the world at a resolution of 1&nbsp;km produced using state-of-the-art model-based statistical methods. Presents estimates (means and 90% confidence intervals) for pH, texture (sa, si, cl), organic carbon and more for 6 depth layers up to 2 m depth. |- | align="left" | [http://www.iiasa.ac.at/Research/LUC/External-World-soil-database/HTML/index.html?sb=1 '''Harmonized World Soil Database'''] || Combines regional and national soil databases and maps under the Land Use Change programme of the [[Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations]]. Includes pH, depth, and texture parameters. 30 [[arc-second]] resolution. |- | align="left" | [http://datadownload.unep-wcmc.org/datasets '''Datasets from the United Nations Environment Programme'''] || Includes global [[ecoregions]], [[wetlands]], distribution of [[coral reefs]], [[mangroves]], and more. |- | align="left" | [http://mrdata.usgs.gov/ '''Mineral Resource Data System'''] || A collection of reports from the [[USGS]] describing metallic and nonmetallic mineral resources throughout the world. Includes names, location, commodity, description, geologic characteristics, production, reserves, and more. |- | align="left" | [http://sourceforge.net/projects/googleworldbank/ '''World Bank Geodata'''] || A wide range of [[World Bank]] datasets: schooling and financial data, etc. |- | align="left" | [http://gadm.org/ '''Global Administrative Areas'''] || Administrative areas in this database are countries and lower level subdivisions such as provinces, departments, bibhag, bundeslander, daerah istimewa, fivondronana, krong, landsvæðun, opština, sous-préfectures, counties, and thana. |- | align="left" | [http://www.sage.wisc.edu/download/sacks/crop_calendar.html '''Crop Calendar Dataset'''] || Raster data on planting dates and harvesting dates across the world for 19 crops. Available at 5 minute and 0.5 degree resolutions. |- | align="left" | [http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/data/collection/aglands '''Global Agriculture Lands'''] || Raster dataset from [[NASA]]'s Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center representing global extent and intensity of use of agricultural lands in 2000. Satellite data from [[MODIS]] and [[SPOT (satellite)]] image vegetation sensor were combined with agricultural inventory data. |- | align="left" | [http://www.iwmigiam.org/info/main/index.asp '''Global Irrigated Area Map (GIAM)'''] || Vector mapping by the [[International Water Management Institute]] of global irrigated and rainfed cropland. |- | align="left" | [http://www.geog.mcgill.ca/~nramankutty/Datasets/Datasets.html '''Past and Present Agricultural Land Use'''] || Multiple datasets showing agricultural land use dating from 1700 to 2007 for 175 crops. |- | align="left" | [https://nelson.wisc.edu/sage/data-and-models/historic-croplands/index.php'''Historic Croplands Dataset, 1700-1992'''] || Documents historical changes in global land cover: croplands from 1700 to 1992. |- | align="left" | [http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/data/set/grand-v1-dams-rev01 '''Global Reservoir and Dam (GRanD) Database'''] || Vector dataset from [[NASA]]'s Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center on all reservoirs with a storage capacity >0.1 cubic km. |- | align="left" | [http://www.acleddata.com/data/ '''Armed Conflict Location and Event Dataset'''] || Contains all reported conflict events in 50 countries in developing world, from 1997 to present. |- | align="left" | [http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/gpw/ '''Gridded Population of the World (GPW)'''] || Dataset from [[NASA]]'s Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center includes raw population, population density, historic, current and predicted. |- | align="left" | [http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/gpw/ '''Global Rural-Urban Mapping Project (GRUMP)'''] || Dataset from [[NASA]]'s Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center (based on the above data, but includes information on rural and urban population balances). |- | align="left" | [http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/data/set/groads-global-roads-open-access-v1 '''Global Roads Open Access Data Set (gROADS)'''] || Well documented global dataset from [[NASA]]'s Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center of roads between settlements using a consistent data model ([[UNSDI]]-T v.2) which is, to the extent possible, topologically integrated, and accurate to approximately 50m. Only roads between settlements are included, not residential streets, and the dataset is suitable for mapping at the 1:250,000 level. |- | align="left" | '''[[OpenStreetMap]]''' || [[Crowdsource]]d data for the whole world including most things you'd find on a standard local paper map: points of interest, buildings, roads and road names, ferry routes etc. |- | align="left" | [http://msi.nga.mil/NGAPortal/MSI.portal?_nfpb=true&_pageLabel=msi_portal_page_62&pubCode=0015 '''World Port Index'''] || Contains the location and physical characteristics of, and the facilities and services offered by major ports and terminals worldwide, from the [[United States]] [[National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency]]. |- | align="left" | [http://openflights.org/data.html '''OpenFlights Airport, Airline and Route Data'''] || Includes all known airports, and a large number of routes between airports (not provided in GIS data formats, but can easily be converted from [[Comma-separated values|CSV]]). |- | align="left" | [http://www.geohive.ie/ '''GeoHive'''] || Population and county statistics (not provided in GIS data formats, but can easily be converted from [[Comma-separated values|CSV]]). |- | align="left" | [http://www.viewfinderpanoramas.org/dem3.html '''Viewfinderpanoramas Digital Elevation Model (DEM) repository'''] || Global [[digital elevation model]] data maintained by [http://www.viewfinderpanoramas.org/ Jonathan de Ferranti]. Major areas of coverage includes: [[Asia]], [[North America]], [[South America]], [[Alps]], [[Northern Hemisphere|North]], [[Europe|Other Europe]], [[Africa]], [[Antarctica]], others.<ref>http://www.viewfinderpanoramas.org/dem3.html Retrieved 2014-05-02</ref> |- |[http://www.chelsa-climate.org/downloads '''CHELSA Climatologies at high resolution for the earth's land surface areas'''] |Global [[Climatological|climatologies]] at 30 arc sec (~1&nbsp;km) resolution for land surface [[temperature]] and [[precipitation]].<ref>{{Cite journal|title=CHELSA climatologies at high resolution for the earth's land surface areas (Version 1.1)|url=http://cera-www.dkrz.de/WDCC/ui/Compact.jsp?acronym=CHELSA_v1_1|journal=|volume=|doi=10.1594/wdcc/chelsa_v1_1}}</ref> Free under the creative commons CC BY license. Files in [[GeoTIFF|GEOTiff]] format |- |'''[https://www.orrbodies.com Orrbodies]''' |Includes geology, topography and mineral occurrence data for several countries as well as globally. Files are mostly in MapInfo format. Both free and commercial datasets available. |- |[https://rextag.com/gis '''Global Energy GIS Data'''] |Covers more than two million miles (3.2 Million Km) of oil and gas [[Pipeline transport|pipelines]], and thousands of energy facilities, such as refineries, LNG terminal, gas processing plants, terminal, and much more. |} == Polar region == {| class="wikitable sortable" |+ '''GIS data for Polar datasets (only)''' |- ! data-sort-type="text" | '''Name''' !! class="unsortable" | '''Description''' |- | [https://www.pgc.umn.edu/data/rema/ REMA] | The Reference Elevation Model of Antarctica (REMA) is a high resolution, time-stamped Digital Surface Model (DSM) of Antarctica at 8-meter spatial resolution. |}
