[[File:VISTA countries locator.svg|thumb|Countries in the proposed emerging markets group of VISTA]] '''VISTA''' is an [[acronym]] for [[Economy of Vietnam|'''V'''ietnam]], [[Economy of Indonesia|'''I'''ndonesia]], [[Economy of South Africa|'''S'''outh Africa]], [[Economy of Turkey|'''T'''urkey]], [[Economy of Argentina|'''A'''rgentina]].<ref name="Promising Post-BRIC Emerging Markets">{{cite web | url=https://www.nri.com/global/opinion/papers/2010/pdf/np2010155.pdf |title=Promising Post-BRIC Emerging Markets | publisher=NRI Papers | accessdate=15 November 2017 | author=Mori, Takeshi}}</ref>
It is used in [[economics]] in discussing [[emerging market]]s.<ref name="the free dictionary">{{cite web | url= http://acronyms.thefreedictionary.com/VISTA | title= VISTA | publisher= The Free Dictionary }}</ref> The concept was first proposed in 2006 by BRICs Economic Research Institute of [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.hywealth.com/en/images/insight/vista.pdf | title= VISTA - Worth a Look | publisher= Henyep International Wealth Management }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url= https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSN1329374420070713 | title= EMERGING FX VIEW-Investors may trade off BRIC for VISTA | publisher= Thomson Reuters | date=13 July 2007 }}</ref>
